      <p>To put this in perspective, a $50,000 balance at 4.75% APY earns roughly $198 per month in passive interest income. That is essentially a free utility payment every month just for choosing the right savings account. Over five years with the same rate and no additional deposits, that $50,000 would grow to approximately $63,230 thanks to compound interest.</p>
      <p>Of course, the real power comes from combining a competitive APY with regular monthly contributions. If you deposit $500 per month into a 4.75% HYSA starting from zero, you would accumulate approximately $6,142 after one year, $12,721 after two years, and $19,756 after three years. Use our <a href="/financial-calculators/compound-interest-calculator/">compound interest calculator</a> to run your own projections with custom deposit amounts and time horizons.</p>
